</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>GWs orders and the request of the Continental Congress committee on fortifying ports for a plan of the harbor at Cape Anne were forwarded to Gridley by Robert Hanson Harrison on 20 April (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>; see also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0089" class="document">GW to the committee, 22 April 1776</a>).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Samuel Hollands Plan of the Harbour And Peninsula of Cape Ann in North America drawn from a Survey is in the map division of the Library of Congress.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0227-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The plans of the Gloucester forts have not been identified.</p>

</div>
